~ contract_galsal_1
do BaseDialougeManager.dialouge_activated.emit()
Galsal: Hi, Do you have something to do??
- Yes
	Galsal: You got a job for me?
	- Yes
		Galsal: You can count me on it
	- No
		Galsal: Oh.. okey
		do BaseDialougeManager.dialouge_deactivated.emit() 
		=> END
- No
	Galsal: ...
do BaseDialougeManager.dialouge_deactivated.emit() 
=> END


~ start_galsal
do BaseDialougeManager.dialouge_activated.emit()
Galsal: [[Hi|Hello|Howdy]], this is TEST dialogue.
Galsal: Here are some choices.
- First one
	Galsal: You picked the first one. 
- Second one
	Galsal: You picked the second one.
- Start again => start_galsal
- End the conversation 
	do BaseDialougeManager.dialouge_deactivated.emit() 
	=> END
	
Galsal: For more information see the online documentation.
do BaseDialougeManager.dialouge_deactivated.emit() 
=> END